gomodel:SYNGO_1883  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 9/11/2017 Pim\n\nFig. 7: BAI1 interacts with cell polarity machinery.\nFig.9: Loss of BAI1 alters Rac1 activation and F-actin in hippocampal neurons.\nFig.10: BAI1 interaction with Par3/Tiam1 is required for spinogenesis and Par3 localization.\nFi.g11: BAI1 signals to Rac1 through Tiam1.. Experimental description: Experiments were done in mouse and rats\nLiteral \"Hippocampal neurons were cultured from E19 Long-Evans rats as described previously.\n\"In utero electroporation was performed as described previously (Hedstrom et al.,2007). We introduced shRNA or vector plasmids\ntogether with pCx-EGFP (CAG promoterdriving EGFP expression) into ICR mice\n(Charles River) at E14.\n\n9/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed BAI1 protein is of human species; \"Human BAI1 was obtained from Y. Nakamura (University of Tokyo) \". Since endogenous rat protein was also visualized annotation is made against rat species." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1883" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

